@node "Intro" "What is ListMaker? What does it do?"

@{b}What is ListMaker? What does it do?@{ub}

 As the name suggests, ListMaker is a List-Maker. (Tough one, eh?) 
 ListMaker v2.3 lets you choose:
 - which directory you want to list
 - whether or not you want comments
 - whether or not you want colourized text
 - whether to add pretyped text, or "realtime text"...
 - type your very own wildcard @{fg fill}(Default #?)@{fg shadow}
 - where to save the file @{fg fill}(Default RAM:)@{fg shadow}
 - ...and what to call it. @{fg fill}(Default FileList.txt)@{fg shadow}

 For more information, press the @{fg shine}Info@{fg shadow} button in the main menu
 of ListMaker...

 Pretty impressive, eh?

 Actually, ListMaker started as a tiny script used to list modules.
 And now, in 1997, it's a pretty big thingy listing just about 
 everything. But I'm still adding more options, so if you have a good 
 idea; @{" contact me! " link Addy}
 
@endnode


