@node "Install" "How to install ListMaker"

@{b}How to install ListMaker:@{ub}

 To install ListMaker, just press the install-button below.
 You @{i}COULD@{ui} also press the icon "ListMaker.Install" in Workbench...

 Anyway, the script will copy all the files ListMaker needs into the 
 C: directory in SYS:.
 (If some of the files already exists, ListMaker will overwrite them.)
 
 No worry though; 
 I've included the latest files I could get my hands on! ;)

 @{" Install ListMaker v2.3 " system "SYS:C/Execute ListMaker.Install"} 

@endnode


@node "Req" "System requirements"

@{b}System requirements:@{ub}

 ListMaker will work on any Amiga with WorkBench v2 or higher.
 Atleast I hope it will, 'coz I've only tried it on a standard 
 A1200 with a 250 meg hd! :)
 (And a A1200 with 18 megz of ram and a 3,2 gig. HD.)

 Also, you need all of the included files, like the ESR-command, 
 the Amigaguide-file, and the PPMore-program.
 (The @{link "install" link Install} script will copy all of these files though!)

@endnode


@node "Features" "ListMaker features"

@{b}ListMakers features:@{ub}

 ListMaker has several cool features.
 Here are some of them:

 @{fg highlight}·@{fg shadow} @{i}Very@{ui} small program
 @{fg highlight}·@{fg shadow} Custom wild-card (ie. ~(#?.(gif|iff|jpg|info|)) )
 @{fg highlight}·@{fg shadow} Fast sorting in alphabetical order
 @{fg highlight}·@{fg shadow} Comments On/Off
 @{fg highlight}·@{fg shadow} Filesize printing
 @{fg highlight}·@{fg shadow} Pretyped/Online text-adding options
 @{fg highlight}·@{fg shadpw} @{fg fill}C@{fg shine}o@{fg fill}l@{fg shine}o@{fg fill}r@{fg shine}i@{fg fill}z@{fg shine}e@{fg fill}d@{fg shadow} text in the list for easy reading! (On/Off function)
 @{fg highlight}·@{fg shadow} "In-program" help (with the "Info"-button)

@endnode


@node "Usage" "How to use ListMaker"

@{b}How to use ListMaker:@{ub}

 To use ListMaker (And create a readable list) simply double-click 
 the ListMaker icon. This will lead to a window popping up in 
 your face, called "ListMaker v2.3". 
 You can now see some text, and three buttons.
 "Yep!" "Info" and "Nah..."

 The "@{fg fill}Yep!@{fg shadow}"-button will start the making of a list, 
 the "@{fg fill}Info@{fg shadow}"-button will display some further information, 
 and the "@{fg fill}Nah...@{fg shadow}"-button will exit the program.

 @{fg highlight}Conserning pretyped text:@{fg shadow}
 When selecting to add pretyped text, the pretyped text should look 
 something like this, or it will not compute;

 @{fg shine}"Hi!*n*nThis is my newest list, updated on the 1st of July!*n"@{fg shadow}

 Just in case you don't know, *n = Enter.
 So the above line would end up like this: 

 @{fg shine}Hi!
  
 This is my newest list, updated on the 1st of July!@{fg shadow}

 If you're having problems coping with this - experiment!
 It's the only way to become really good at something!
 
@endnode


@node "Bugs" "Known bugs"

@{b}Known bugs:@{ub}

 To this day there are some minor bugs. 
 These bugs I have been unable to fix, but if you know how to fix 'em, 
 please @{" email me " link Addy}!
 
 @{fg highlight}The known bugs are:
 - @{fg shadow}If a filename and/or comment is longer than the allowed space 
   (Filename = 28, Comment = 38, Filesize = 8)
   it will adjust the page.
   Ie. if the filename is longer than the allowed space, it will move 
   the comments (and the filesize) to the right. 
   Example: (in smaller scale than real-life!)

   @{fg shine}Filename        Comment            Filesize
   Filename        Comment            Filesize
   FilenameTooLong   Comment            Filesize@{fg shadow}

   As you can see, the bottom line is somewhat misplaced. 
   This is because it has a much too big filename.
   But, by selecting "No comments", the filename space increases with 
   10 spaces.
   
   However, this "bug" can be fixed with a normal text-editor,
   allowing you to chop the filenames and comments in size.

 @{fg highlight}-@{fg shadow} When selecting a wildcard (ie. "~(#?.(bak|info|auts))")
   it will only be enforced within the selected drawer, not all of the
   subdrawers. 
   Example:
   
   You select to list all of your GFX.
   The gfx is stored within a drawer called "GFX", which in turn 
   contains 4 drawers; "JPG", "GIF", "IFF" and "MISC".

   When listing the "GFX"-drawer with the wildpattern 
   "~(#?.(bak|info|auts))", it will not remove the .bak's, info's and
   auts' in "JPG", "GIF", "IFF" and "MISC", only DIRECTLY within 
   the "GFX"-drawer. 

 And that raps it up! Luckily, ListMaker v2.3 doesn't contain any more 
 (known!) bugs, but if you know the solution to ANY of these problems/
 bugs, please email me.
 It would really help me out.

@endnode


@node "Note" "An important note"

@{b}An important note:@{ub}

 To enable me to make further updates/new versions of ListMaker, 
 I am dependent of your support. 
 "Your support" can be anything from a nice letter to a harsh 
 bugreport, but it will without a doubt excite me enough to make
 a new version of ListMaker. 
 Without "coder's" like myself, the Amiga will surely die due
 to insufficient amounts of programs, games and utilities. 
 I know you've all heard this before, but it's true. The vast 
 majority of Amiga users are consumers, not producers. 
 It's your job as a consumer to encourage the producer; failing can and
 will affect @{fg fill}you@{fg shadow}.

 Without any proof that there really exists ListMaker-users out there, 
 I cannot, and I will not, continue to develop ListMaker.
 Why should I, if nobody's using it?

 I ask you show your enthusiasm towards program-development on Amiga 
 by sending me a postcard, letter, suggestion, bug-report, short story
 or similar to the following address:

 @{fg shine}Erling Lĝken Andersen
 @{fg fill}Fiskegt.14
 1515 Moss
 Norway@{fg shadow}

 @{fg fill}Phone/Fax:@{fg shadow} (+ 47 if outside Norway) 69 27 35 86
 @{fg fill}Email:@{fg shadow} zerling@hotmail.com@{fg shadow}

 If you send a disk with a @{fg shine}nice@{fg shadow} letter on it
 (and perhaps your own program?) you will receive the latest version
 of ListMaker. Please state which version you already have.

 Thank you.

 @{b}NOTE:@{ub} Another favour I ask from you, is that you spread this program 
 as much as you can. Feel free to add it to any Fred Fish disk, 
 upload it to any BBS or just copy it to your friend.
 This way a lot of people will receive the program, and perhaps 
 @{i}some@{ui} of them will send me a letter. :) (Or something...)

@endnode

@node "New" "What next? What can be improved?"

@{b} What next? What can be improved?@{ub}

 For the next version of ListMaker @{" (If there will be one!) " link Note}
 I was thinking on several things. Some of these include:
 - "A decrunch archive and list it" built-in function. 
   This could be handy if you wann'a list archives, and stuff like that.
 - A menu letting you choose which @{fg fill}textviewer@{fg shadow} to use...
 - Eighter a password-screen, or a file-checking system, so the 
   whole, unedited ListMaker is distributed!

 But hey! It all depends on you: If you send me a nice postcard
 (perhaps from where you live???) letting me know that you are using
 ListMaker, and interested in further development, I will make a new 
 version, and send it to you. (Just add a disk, though!)

 @{" Press here for the address! " link Addy}

@endnode


@node "Author" "Who's 'da man behind 'da program?"

@{b}Who's 'da man behind 'da program?@{ub}

 Hi. My name is Erling Lĝken Andersen. (or PSyChO if you wish...)
 At the present time I am a member of Apathy and Instinct
 (two norwegian scene groups...), working as a grafician.
 In @{i}real@{ui} life I am a student, 16 years of age on the 
 18th of may, and working part-time as a traffic-guard.

 I've had an Amiga for 7 years now, and my current machine
 is an Amiga 1200 with a 250 megabyte hd.
 But, since my current machine is pretty crap (Low memory!) I'm 
 going to upgrade soon.

 Also, I would like to mention Harald Kuhr in the "author"-section.
 He has helped me a @{b}lot@{ub} with the coding of thiz program, 
 and without him, you probably wouldn't be reading thiz right now.
 So go ahead; Thank him!

 And... I would like to point out the fact that some of the included 
 files, like the ESR-command, is NOT made by me, but other - just as 
 talented - coders. These coders are:
 
 @{" ESR " link ESR} İ 1993 Scott Ellis (Easy String Requester v1.0)
 PPMore İ 19xx Nico François (PowerPacker More v1.8a)
 RequestChoice, RequestFile and AmigaGuide probably İ Commodore, 
 or whoever NOW owns the Amiga. 
 (@{"Gateway 2000" link Gate}, is it?)

@endnode

